==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crucial
<hw>Cru"cial</hw> <pr>(kr?"sh<it>a</it>l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>crucial</ets>, fr. L. <ets>crux</ets>, <ets>crucis</ets>, cross,
torture. See <er>Cross</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the form of
a cross; appertaining to a cross; cruciform; intersecting; <as>as,
<ex>crucial</ex> ligaments; a <ex>crucial</ex> incision</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Severe; trying or searching, as if bringing to the
cross; decisive; <as>as, a <ex>crucial</ex> test</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crucian carp</ent>⟦br⟧
